DULINI grabbed command early and set a pressured pace towards the rail, was headed near the three eighths, kept on for a bit further then faltered entering the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: REMEMBERING WILBUR settled four wide while not too far back of the dueling leaders, advanced five wide under coaxing into the stretch, drifted in briefly near mid stretch, corrected and sustained under solid handling, took over inside the sixteenth pole and drew clear at the wire. MONTAUK DADDY had speed then rated just off the embattled leaders, tracked two wide mid turn, angled four wide and launched a bid entering the lane, gained a slim advantage inside the three sixteenths, got the better of FLAMING EAST leaving mid stretch, dug in when confronted by the winner from the outside, fought on past the sixteenth marker and gave way grudgingly. CALL ME MAESTRO broke a step slow, trailed three wide into the turn, shifted in some around the turn, move up past mid stretch and kept on with some effort to earn the show. FLAMING EAST was sent up to the inside of rivals to take a slim early lead, set a pressured pace in the two path, dueled past the five sixteenths, brushed with LANTAU soon into the stretch, kept up the fight past the furlong grounds then gave way very late. JIMMY THE KID rated off the leaders after an alert break, chased towards the inside and failed to drum up a rally. LITTLE BAY broke a step slow, raced three wide leaving the far turn and failed to menace. LANTAU had speed three wide and contested the pace outside FLAMING EAST, stayed on past the quarter pole, exchanged a brush in upper stretch then tired through the final furlong. PER RULING FROM THE MARYLAND RACING COMMISSION, MONTAUK DADDY WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARIA FROM MIAMI , with the pace three deep and under rating, responded to stout asking in upper stretch and kicked well clear, wandered outward under left handed encouragement through the final sixteenth, met an outside challenge from ROYAL PARTY in deep stretch and got the perfect bob. ROYAL PARTY drifted out a bit at the break then checked when pinched, recovered and trailed two wide leaving the far turn, gathered some momentum past the five sixteenths, swung out five wide into the lane, straightened away, closed gamely through the final furlong, drew alongside the winner in deep stretch and got the bad end of the nose bob. SUPER JO JO broke sharply and took a short lead between foes, dueled between runners into and around the turn, stayed on to mid stretch then weakened. SNOOZE BUTTON was urged along inside a pair of runners while contesting the pace, fought on into the lane, failed to keep pace past mid stretch and gave way. SK'S HEART , three wide nearing the turn, pursued the duelers around the turn and gave way. BIZ AS USUAL was outrun. AZTEC BAY saved ground with early pursuit, dropped back after appearing to shy from the rail nearing the turn, saved ground into the lane, faded and was reported by the stewards to have bled. SONNY AND MAX gave early chase four wide and retreated around the turn.
